\c 3
\s1 Kurban Persekutuan
\p
\v 1 "Apabila persembahan yang kamu bawa kepada TUHAN itu untuk memelihara persekutuan yang baik dengan Dia, kamu dapat membawa seekor sapi jantan atau seekor sapi dari kawanan ternakmu - tambahkan ternak, tambahkanlah, tetapi apa yang Anda hadirkan kepada Yahweh harus menjadi hewan yang tidak memiliki cacat
\v 2 You must bring the animal to the entrance to the Sacred Tent. You must lay your hands on its head. Then you must slaughterit \add and drain some of its blood in a bowl\add*. Then one of Aaron's sons, one of the priests, will sprinkle the blood against all sides of the altar.
\v 3 From that offering you must bring to Yahweh a sacrifice that will be burned in the fire. That will consist of all the fat that covers the inner parts of the animal, or which is attached to them—
\v 4 the kidneys and the fat that is attached to them near the lower back muscle, and the fat that covers the liver.
\v 5 Then one of the priests will burn those things on the altar, along with the other parts of the animal that will becompletely burned to be an offering \add to Yahweh\add*. And the aroma while it burns will be pleasing to Yahweh.
\p
\v 6 If that offering to maintain good fellowship with Yahweh is a sheep or a goat, it must also be an animal that has no defects.
\v 7 If you offer a lamb, you must present it to Yahweh \add at the entrance to the SacredTent\add*. You must lay your hands on the lamb's head and then slaughterit.\add You must drain some of its blood in a bowl\add*.
\v 8 Then one of the priests will sprinkle that blood against all sides of the altar.
\v 9 From that offering you must separate these things to be a sacrifice to Yahweh that is burned: Its fat, the fat tail that you must cut off close to the backbone, and all the fat that covers the inner parts of the lamb or which is attached to them—
\v 10 the kidneys with the fat that is on them near the lower back muscle, and the fat that covers the liver.
\v 11 One of the priests will burn those things on the altar to be an offering to Yahweh;\add it will be as though\add* they are food \add given to Yahweh\add*.
\p
\v 12 If your offering is a goat, you must take/present it to Yahweh.
\v 13 You must lay your hands on its head. Then you must slaughter it in front of the Sacred Tent. Then one of Aaron's sons will sprinkle the blood against all sides of the altar.
\v 14 From that offering you must separate these things to be a sacrifice to Yahweh that is burned: All the fat that covers the inner parts of the animal or which is attached to them,
\v 15 the kidneys with the fat that is on them near the lower back muscle, and the fat that covers the liver.
\v 16 The priest will burn those things on the altar to be an offering to Yahweh;\add it will be as though\add* they are food \add given to Yahweh\add*. And the aroma while it burns will be pleasing toYahweh. All the fat \add of the animals that are sacrificed\add* belongs to Yahweh.
\p
\v 17 This is a command that must be obeyed by you and your descendants forever, wherever you live: You must not eat the fat orthe blood \add of any animal\add*.”